Overpriced
Great jambalaya!

formattedAddress: 601 Queen Anne Ave N (at Mercer St)

tip.text: Super awesome vibe and coffee. Taste the danishes. Come here at night. It's really popular and buzzing

contact.facebookName: 프릳츠 커피 컴퍼니 - Fritz Coffee Company

tip.text: I had the popular option. Pictured. Very very sweet and very nice owners. Would recommend on a cold day.
Wifi not available at 12-2 but otherwise trendy spot. Coffee above average but not amazing
Some of the best coffee I've had.. and I'm from Australia
Really wonderful cafe I found on a business trip to Canberra. Would recommend the spiced eggs with smoked salmon. Yum!

contact.facebookName: Two Before Ten -  Cafe & Coffee Roasters

tip.text: Quite tasty food, obviously quite expensive, but great location. I recommend the seafood (crab) but not so much the pork.
Waiter was super rude and the Asian wasn't particularly authentic at all. Pad Thai had tiny prawns and was way too saucy
Great value for money! 7.5 euros for all you can eat. It's all fresh and quite tasty. No fruit though when I went (winter)
Elk soup and hot wine is a must. Not just for the food but also for the cool medival interior.
Authentic indian! Quite tasty with some meals that have a little latvian touch. I would recommend the rides and potato and lentil based dishes. Vege only
Best place to get lunch. Not only cheap but healthy. 4.2euros for a hot meal with vegetables, meat and your choice of barley or potato. New variety every week
The buffet here is around 10euros and the food is very high quality. Definitely recommend going here. It's one of the best places in Riga.
Wonderful place to eat. The food is a little pricey but looks great. Definitely come here for a seaside chill.
Becoming one of my favorite bars. Met one of the managers and he came and gave us free drinks for coming. Great vibe and interior. Would recommend!
I came here to hear what all the fuss was about and I was not disappointed. The toasties were tasty and beautiful in their simplicity. Service was great. Look forward to coming here again
Hidden gem! Cute little beach.
The ramen is large and cheap for student. Just show your card. The eggs seemed a little pricey and the miso was very salty. I would recommend but menya in the city is superior.

contact.facebookName: Manpuku Sydney 麺処　万福

tip.text: Good set of gym equipment. Nice place to work out whilst watching the dogs play.
Fucking love this place. When I was there there was sand on the floor. Great drunk selection and great offbeat food. Good for a group or just a couple of people catching up. Beds in a bar too!
Simple ramen in a food court but damn is the soup good. Great value, tasty pork and well made noodles. Would prefer a nicer location.
Ridiculously good value, the service yeah it's shit but just order, go to the top level and wait till it comes.
Had the pad thai, it was average but the service was fine and the price was okay. Good for a quick meal.
One of the best and most affordable hotels I've been. This was a mystery deal and they gave us a massive room with amazing bed and bathroom.
Bakery is okay, it has typical Asian food and baked goods. The breakfast is nice and has good value, there's something off with the place though
Cheap fresh udon! Similar to mappen in the city but with better service and interior. Try the cheap chicken rice bowl!
Great burgers and soups, poor service, I would recommend taking the good and walking down to the water.
My favorite cafe in the world. Excellent study place, great breakfast; try the tortilla de patatas. Come here for a drink in the evenings. Can't recommend enough.
Amazing Cuban food. The owners are very friendly. Try the pulled pork and fried bananas with rice!
Cheap authentic udon. Best for a quick bite. One of my favorites.
The ramen here is amazing, great hidden away place, healthy salad options too.
Nice service! Get the Turkish tea🍵☕️👍
